Preprocessing - Module1¶

In [6]:
def cleaning_numbers(text):
    return re.sub('[0-9]+', '', text)
In [7]:
def cleaning_characters(text):
    return re.sub(r'[^0-9a-zA-Z ]','', text)
In [8]:
def cleaning_stopwords(text):
    stop_words = stopwords.words('english')
    return " ".join([word for word in str(text).split() if word not in stop_words])
In [9]:
def remove_punctuations(text):
    for punc in string.punctuation:
        text = text.replace(punc, "")
    return text
In [10]:
def repeat(text):
    return re.sub(r'(.)\1+',r'\1', text)
In [11]:
def preprocessing(doc):
    doc = doc.str.lower()
    doc = doc.apply(lambda t: remove_punctuations(t))
    doc = doc.apply(lambda t: cleaning_numbers(t))
    doc = doc.apply(lambda t: cleaning_characters(t))
    doc = doc.apply(lambda t: cleaning_stopwords(t))
    doc = doc.apply(lambda tx: repeat(tx))
    return doc
In [12]:

lm = nltk.WordNetLemmatizer()
def Lemmatize_text(text):
    return [lm.lemmatize(w) for w in text]
  
df['review1'] = df['review1'].apply(lambda t: Lemmatize_text(t))

# create a function to combine the values of the columns sentiment and genre into a single string 
def get_important_features(data):
    important_features =[]
    for i in range(0,data.shape[0]):
        important_features.append(data['sentiment'][i] + ' ' + data['genre'][i])
    return important_features

    movie_title = df[df.index == item[0]]['title'].values[0]
    print(j+1, movie_title)
    j=j+1
    if j>6:
        break

def preprocess(sent):
    sent = nltk.word_tokenize(sent)
    sent = nltk.pos_tag(sent)
    return sent
